mpliance throughout the region.\r\n\r\n· Mediating disputes between EPA and local communities concerning  proposed Superfund actions.  Ms. Cox managed ICF's Conflict Management Services practice [$3.8 million annually].  Ms. Cox mediates site specific disputes related to the Superfund program.  Key actors in these community-based disputes are interviewed and a conflict assessment is prepared.  Based upon an analysis of the effectiveness of using mediation/facilitation, she will move forward to try to convene the parties in conflict and mediate a settlement. \r\n\r\n· Designing a negotiated permitting project for a resource recovery facility subject to Rhode Island state and local permit requirements.\r\n\r\n· Designing and facilitating a meeting of academic, scientific, and technical experts from around the country to discuss the key issues associated with the use of a "risk-based" approach to the development of RCRA Landfill Disposal regulations.\r\n· \r\n	2015-02-27 05:24:50.620452	2015-02-27 05:24:50.620452	327
