l, Michigan.  Project resulted in the creation of the project’s final report: Planning for the Future: A Reuse Planning Report for the Plainwell Paper Mill.\r\n\r\n• Assisted the Town of Fort Edward and EPA Region 2 with a two-part overlay analysis and adaptive use analysis highlighting opportunities to integrate community planning efforts and EPA's remedial priorities at the Hudson River PCBs Superfund site to address and minimize potential community impacts from the dredging of the portion of the site located adjacent to the Town of Fort Edward, New York.  Project responsibilities included project design, coordination and facilitation of community meetings, conducting of site and market analyses, and development of the project’s final report.\r\n\r\n• Managed community involvement process for the Former Spellman Engineering site in Orlando, Florida; developed six-member Neighborhood Advisory Committee (NAC); coordinated and co-facilitated two NAC meetings and a public meeting; conducted site and community analyses; and developed educational materials for project meetings.	2015-02-27 05:24:34.790367	2015-02-27 05:24:34.790367	20
