1110	Brian	K	Petroff	bpetroff@kumc.edu			3901 Rainbow Boulevard		Kansas City	KS	66160	0	Researcher	Center for Reproductive Sciences, Ohio State University	0	(Source: http://www.kumc.edu/physiology/petroff.html)\r\n\r\nThe majority of my research is focused upon the impact of environmental toxicants on female fertility. Dioxins are one of most worrisome classes of these toxicants and can decrease fertility by interfering with ovulation. In addition to preventing ovulation at quite low doses, dioxins exhibit chemoprotective properties for some hormone-dependent cancers. Research goals are to understand the mechanisms of dioxin action on the female reproductive system and develop novel compounds that retain the contraceptive and chemoprotective properties of dioxins while avoiding their toxicities. In addition to this reproductive toxicology and contraception research program, I collaborate to investigate the role of Src tyrosine kinase in ovarian follicular development.	2015-02-27 05:24:55.148662	2015-02-27 05:24:55.148662	404
