1161	Nora		Chiong	nora.chiong@plexusli.com	757-287-9569		140 Seaside Lane		Virginia Beach	VA	23462	50	Certified Government Meeting Professional & PM	Plexus	13	Duties and Responsibilities\r\nMs. Chiong is a Program Manager at Plexus LI, a wholly owned subsidiary of Plexus Scientific Corporation created for the specific purpose of fostering sustainability initiatives.  \r\nKnowledge, Skills, and Experience  \r\nAs a Program Manager, Ms. Chiong has negotiated a variety of contracts from cradle to grave, prepared, submitted and tracked invoicing on delivery orders, provided support to more than 150 on-site contractors and government clients, processed travel and expense reports, and assisted in writing of proposals.  Ms. Chiong was also responsible for processing all new hire and termination paperwork, negotiating benefit renewals and ensuring compliance with all EEO laws. \r\nMs. Chiong is also a Professional Facilitator and Certified Government Meeting Professional with over twelve years experience coordinating and facilitating conferences and Tier I/II partnering workshop nation-wide.  Her areas of expertise include coordinating workshops, organizing conferences, and facilitating inter-agency partnering between environmental regulators and Federal agencies.  She has extensive experience in team building, group process development, conflict resolution, and performance improvement methods and systems.    Provides workshop support and oversight to the US Army Reserve Command (USARCOM), Installation Management Command – Army Reserve (IMCOM-AR), US Army Environmental Command (USAEC), National Guard Bureau (NGB), Office of the Federal Environmental Executive (OFEE) and US Army Corps of Engineers (USACE). Duties include:  identifying and selecting meeting locations; securing hotel accommodations at the government per diem rate; negotiating hotel contracts; coordinating with hotels to provide meeting space and AV equipment; managing room blocks; BEO’s; putting together group